Perun Consultants is the leading independent advisory firm with offices in Hong Kong and Singapore. We specialise in provision of high quality services in the areas of forensic accounting, corporate advisory, restructuring, turnaround and liquidation appointments. At Perun, we promote a work-life balance, value individualism and embrace the differences.
We are currently seeking an ambitious and qualified candidate with the following attributes to join our Hong Kong office as a Restructuring and Insolvency Manager / Assistant Manager / Associate

Responsibilities:

day-to-day administration of different compulsory and voluntary liquidations, bankruptcy receiverships, and/or restructuring engagements
drafting reports to the Court and other deliverables to clients;
contributing to development of best practice;
establishing and developing client network; and
coaching and training junior staff.
Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree or higher in Accounting, Finance, Law or other Business-related discipline preferred.
CA, CPA or equivalent. Consideration will also be given to part qualified candidates, with support given to complete the qualification process;
5+ years relevant experience including insolvency, restructuring and forensic accounting for the position of Assistant Manager and above and 2+ years relevant experience for the position of Associate.
Good business sense and commercial acumen;
Strong problem solving skills;
Strong financial, business analytical and excellent report writing skills; and
Excellent written and oral communication skills in both English and Mandarin Chinese.
The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate solid experience (commensurate with the applicable employment grade) in:

insolvency, financial and operational restructuring and/or other advisory engagements. Experience in complex cross-border matters would be advantageous;
administration of compulsory and voluntary liquidations, bankruptcy receiverships, and/or restructuring assignments;
drafting reports, letters and other deliverables;
client management from a professional services background.
In addition to the above role, we are always interested in hearing from proactive, commercially minded, individuals at all levels of seniority and experience looking to work in a dynamic and flexible environment.

We offer a competitive remuneration package where you will be rewarded for your individual and team performance. We are committed to being an inclusive employer and are happy to consider flexible working arrangements.
To apply, contact us at Apply Now .

