• Self-motivated, proactive and mature;
• Proficient in Microsoft office applications;
• Strong financial, business analytical and report writing skills; and
• Excellent written and oral communication skills in both English and Mandarin Chinese, including both technical and business writing.
The successful candidate will possess technical knowledge of financial accounting practices and be able to demonstrate experience (commensurate with the applicable employment grade) with the following:

Assessment and quantification of losses and potential damage awards;
Valuation and appraisal of assets;
Design and evaluation of financial forecast models;
Report writing;
Providing litigation support services, working closely with legal counsel, law enforcement officers and regulatory agencies; and
Assisting with internal and external investigations.
Insolvency-related experience; and
Assisting with internal and external investigations.

In addition to the above role, we are always interested in hearing from proactive, commercially minded, individuals at all levels of seniority and experience looking to work in a dynamic and flexible environment.

